# Bridge environment variables
#
# Bridge's dashboard runs on seeded data with no env vars. The Operation
# Anniversary reservation system (Ruby) needs Supabase — fill these in to go live.

# ── Supabase (client-safe, exposed to the browser) ───────────────────────────
# Supabase project URL, e.g. https://xxxxxxxx.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
# Supabase anon/public key (RLS keeps the reservations table closed; customers
# only reach it through the get_availability() / book_reservation() functions)
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# ── Server-only secrets (NEVER prefixed NEXT_PUBLIC; never sent to the client) ─
# Service-role key — used only in server actions / route handlers for staff
# admin reads & writes. Do NOT commit a real value. Do NOT expose to the browser.
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=
# Shared staff passcode for the reservation admin gate (server-verified only).
ADMIN_PASSCODE=
